21/11/2010
BUCHAREST, Romania -- The National Anti-Corruption Agency announced Friday (November 19th) they have detained a businessman suspected of offering a bribe to a senior official at the interior ministry.
According to the announcement, the man tried to give 50,000 euros to ministry official Dan Fatuloiu in return for resolving legal cases.
Local media identified the businessman as Catalin Chelu.
According to reports, he was arrested along with three other individuals.
Chelu is estimated to be worth 17m euros.
(AP, Realitatea, Hotnews.ro, Libertatea, Adevarul - 19/11/10)
